## Decisions made
- **Q1 ‚Äî defer teacher import to slice 10.** The Invitation table can't
  carry staffNumber/specialty per phase-1.md:478 ("No new columns are
  added to invitations"), and the slice 8 spec at line 950 requires
  both. Spec is internally inconsistent. Slice 10 ships TeacherProfile
  + the full teacher import together. Phase 1 deliverables don't
  require teacher bulk-import.
- **Q2 ‚Äî single Admission Number column; sibling case handled by
  Guardian dedup.** Two CSV rows for the same parent with different
  studentAdmissionNumber ‚Üí ONE Guardian + TWO StudentGuardian links.
  Naturally expressed, simpler than multi-link, spec-aligned.
- **Q3 ‚Äî symmetric `/guardians/import` route**, plus two CTAs:
  bulk-import link on the student-detail Guardians tab (the place
  admins spend most of their guardian time), and a sub-line on the
  /students/import help card pointing at the guardian wizard.
- **Q4 ‚Äî guardian Zod row schema** (required: firstName, lastName,
  relationship, phone, studentAdmissionNumber; optional: email,
  occupation, employer, address, notes, isPrimary, canPickup) plus a
  12-field synonym table including "ward" / "ward adm no" idioms for
  the link column.
- **Two design divergences from the spec** (Q2-related), both captured
  inline in code + in `docs/deferred.md`:
  - **Dedup key is `(phone, firstName, lastName)`**, not the spec's
    `(phone, lastName)`. Schema slice 5 comment explicitly anticipates
    parents sharing a household phone + surname; the spec key
    collapses Mr. + Mrs. Okonkwo into one Guardian. Inline pointer
    added at phase-1.md:949.
  - **First-row-wins** when dedup key matches but Guardian-level
    fields disagree (relationship, email, etc.). Schema puts
    relationship on Guardian, not on the link ‚Äî find-or-create
    semantics force a choice and first-wins is the simplest honest
    one. Tested explicitly.
- **One unexpected during cp1 ‚Äî circular import bug.** Refactor had
  `students/import.ts` value-re-exporting `STUDENT_IMPORT_DATE_FORMATS`
  etc. from `../imports/index.js`. CommonJS load chain hit the value
  re-export while `students/import.js` was mid-load, so the
  apply-mapping schema was built with `z.enum(undefined)`. 17 existing
  tests went red with the cryptic "Cannot read properties of undefined
  (reading 'map')". Fix: only TYPE-only re-exports from
  `students/import.ts`; the one external value-level consumer
  (apps/web/.../mapping/page.tsx) now imports `IMPORT_DATE_FORMATS`
  directly. Comment block in students/import.ts warns the next
  refactor away.

